<br>
Eandori, I don't think you understand how focus items are coded. they DO have all the same effect, wich is &quot;summon stronger pet&quot;. Using a focus staff or the gloves of dark summoning on a greater voc pet will yield the exact same result. The focus items are tied to spells (see lucy for reference), so you'll notice that low level pet spells are tied to sol ro focus items, staves to the 49-60 pets and gloves of dark summoning to gvoc, epic and PoP pets. There is no lack of coding, all they would need to do to make staves affect post 60 spell is add the &quot;focus staff xxx&quot; ID to the spell it would focus. They curent way is very much by design, and not a lack of added code.<br>
<br>
Odibil, there is a focus item for epic, and it's the gloves of dark summoning from VT.<br>
<br>
Gurglespit, I disagree with the way you see epic, and let me list again for people who are now in PoP. Of course epic are still cool for people in their 50s fighting in velious, that is the scale of epics.<br>
<br>
rogue - 13 dmg piercer are very weak by today's standards. Good piercer by now is 17 dmg, and all haste item have 41% (the ones above CoF wich is what a post-epic rogue will have)<br>
Druid - Free DoT, but so slow and weak most don't bother using<br>
Necro - Free DoT, but same comment as druids, plus it's so ugly no necro wants it, the real necro epic is zlandicar's heart.<br>
Chanter - No chanter in his right mind will use shissar unless in the rare case where he is oom and need to buff NOW. There is no reason to use snake staff when they have group shissar, vallon, group vallon and even an item that only drops in tier2 planes and cast a better haste than shissar.<br>
Ranger - Oh ya, ranger slow proc is usefull in PoP.... NoT!<br>
warrior - war epic is not only &quot;not great..&quot;, it's gimptastic, it was not worth getting when it came out, even less now, you can get better weapons than war epic in 6 man xp groups in velious.<br>
Paladin - knight weapons from tov and up are so far ahead of epic no hybrid in his right mind would wield one nowadays.<br>
Shadowknight - same as pallies  <br>
Bard - It's good for lazy bards, for bard who want to maximize their songs, they use post-epic instruments with better mods.<br>
Shaman - Free Dot, but so sucky a JBB from sebilis will easily outdamage it.<br>
Wizard - Wiz is one of the only epic still really being used, I'll give you that<br>
Cleric - Cleric epic is a raid item, it gives nothing really to the wielder.<br>
Monks- Still usefull to an extent.<br>
Beastlords - Pathetic compared to even low end luclin bst weapons.<br>
Mages - Still situationally usefull, lost a lot of it's status with PoP pets (finally).<br>
<br>
So out of 15 epics, only 4 are really still useful in PoP (cleric, monk, wizard, bard (to some extent)). No I don't count mana free dots from kunark era to be usefull in the high DPS state PoP is built around. I have epic on my shaman, and outside from killing kunark type crap, it's not very useful, and that's at 53, imagine at 65. So that leaves us with 11/15 epic who are outdated by PoP contents, as it should really... KUNARK gear vs. PoP gear... hmmm wonder wich one should be better...<br>
<br>
Face reality please, epic is KUNARK gear, repeat after me, KUNARK... we are in PoP now, 3 expansion later... sure your kunark gear is not as strong as it was in sebilis, live with it, that's normal evolution in a mmorpg. Epics are doable in the mid 50s... Mage epic still has it's strenght. It's, BY FAR, the best pet you can get before lvl 61. It's still even post PoP, the most well-rounded pet. It's still a very decent stat item for the level at wich you can get it. It's still a mana free pet. It's still the most damaging pet from the front if it's proc can land (so up to mobs lvl 62-63 or so). <br>
<br>
For those bringing in the &quot;I lose 5 focus item to get epic&quot;. Your argument is not valid. Those 5 focus items only work up to lvl 60, so does epic, and up to level 60, epic is way way way way more powerful than those 5 focus items, so the whole point is moot. For the range at wich those focus work, the epic pet is far superior, so you are not losing focus items, you are gaining a pet MUCH stronger than those focus items would give you.<br>
<br>
Yes epic is easy by now, time does not equal difficulty. If you don't have the patience to camp for epic part, too bad for you, cause it's certainly not hard for a mage to solo most of the epic quest. Time-consuming, yes, hard, no. It's a choice you have, would you rather spend time doing the quest and have a godly pet that will make you kick ass till level 61, or invest that time in leveling and never having a pet that owns normal pets.<br>
