A level 65 warrior with 200 AA WILL INDEED do more damage with his epic then a level 60 warrior with 0 AA. <br>
****<br>
<br>
You forget one thing, a lvl 65 warrior with 200 AA will not be using epic, in fact, I highly doubt any 60+ warriors still use epic.<br>
<br>
****<br>
Please note in my original post, I said the effect DOES NOT have to the same as other focus effects. If you desire a Kunark particle weapon to not have the focus ability of Gloves of Dark summoning, then fine. Other focus effects could be added of lesser value then that item<br>
****<br>
<br>
Please note you totaly ignore the way pet focus items are coded, they do not do anything by themselves, it's the spell that have 2 possible outcome, 1 normal, and 1 focussed. What you are asking for is a complete re-coding of the pet focus code. Making sol ro focus item work on 61-65 pets would not make them have the same effect as they did on lvl 34 pets, it would have the SAME effect as the gloves of dark summoning from VT. That is the way it's coded. Gloves or dark summoning add a level to epic, making him 50. However, those same gloves don't add a level to lvl 61-65 pets, they make the pet hit for harder and have more hp, etc. The focus effect is not tied to the item, it's tied to the spell. So you can't have the things you ask unless they recode all of the focus item code and part of the spell-casting code.<br>
<br>
****<br>
How do you know for sure that there are no drops in POP that focus pets?<br>
****<br>
<br>
Because they are shown in the spell file. Like I said before in this very thread, the focus are tied to the spells, not the items. It's very easy to go to lucy and look at the 61-65 pets and see that the only linked focus item (there's room for 2 btw) are the gloves or dark summoning.<br>
<br>
****<br>
While I like this idea, and it does make sense, some say it is too old an item. However leaving the Gloves of Dark Summoning as a focus effect on post 60 pets is the same thing. A prior expansion.<br>
****<br>
<br>
You are comparing a 4 expansion old item to a 1 expansion old item (wich is, incidentaly, found in the last zone you will explore in that expansion, if you ever get there), so no, it is not even close to being the same thing.<br>
<br>
****<br>
If a melee can wear a flowing black sash for haste, which was even BEFORE KUNARK, why can't a mage focus a pet with a focus item?<br>
****<br>
<br>
I agree with the principle, but I highly doubt Sony will invest the time (wich is much bigger than you seem to think) to change such a frivolous thing as pet focus. Imho by far the best course of action for VI would be to indeed add other focus for post 61 pets, each dropping in it's respective elemental plane and focussing only that type of pet.<br>
<br>
****<br>
While this game is continually expanding along the leading edge, old content isn't phased out per sae, it just isn't used or considered 'cool' anymore, much. <br>
****<br>
<br>
