<br>
This is the way pet focus items work.<br>
<br>
1. You cast a pet spell (with 2 possible outcome, petA and petB (petB is the focussed pet).<br>
2. The game check if you have the focus item for that spell.<br>
3. If you don't have the focus item, petA is summoned, if you have the focus item, petB is summoned.<br>
<br>
Wich is very different from the summon petA and add X stats, hp, level, etc depending on focus item. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721">Woon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://tde.e-slackers.net/">&lt;TDE&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
